0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 46 "4.  Binomial Theorem
.  Use the Maple command  " }{TEXT 291 6 "expand" }{TEXT 285 2 "  " }
{TEXT -1 34 "to calculate the expansion of     " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)
^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 63 "    for values n=1..
10 .  In each case use the Maple command   " }{TEXT 286 7 "coeffs " }
{TEXT 293 1 " " }{TEXT -1 84 "to pick off the coefficients.   For exam
ple,  if n=5 we would execute the following:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "expand((a+b)^5);\ncoeffs(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#,.*$)%\"aG\"\"&\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&\"\"%F(%\"bGF(F(*(\"#5F
()F&\"\"$F()F,\"\"#F(F(*(F.F()F&F2F()F,F0F(F(*(F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F
'F(F(" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6(\"#5\"\"&F#\"\"\"F%F$" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "Do the rest from 1 to 10.   " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "Note:  it is possible to use a " }{TEXT 292 9 "for
 loop " }{TEXT -1 69 " to simplify this task since we are doing a repe
titive calculation.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "Note:  Also, the
 the command " }{TEXT 294 6 "coeffs" }{TEXT -1 15 " unfortunately " }
{TEXT 295 8 "does not" }{TEXT -1 36 " pick off the coefficients in ord
er." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The
 " }{TEXT 288 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for
 finding the coefficients of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^
n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 
296 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is relatively obvious that the coefficie
nt of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^k*b^(n-k);" "6#*&)%\"aG%\"kG\"\"\")%\"bG,&%
\"nGF'F&!\"\"F'" }{TEXT -1 19 "  for any value of " }{TEXT 297 1 "k" }
{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 298 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by \+
the number of ways we can choose " }{TEXT 299 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of t
he " }{TEXT 301 1 "a" }{TEXT -1 12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 300 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 302 1 "a" }{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }
{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }
{TEXT -1 4 " ), " }{TEXT 303 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number
 of combinations of " }{TEXT 304 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing
 " }{TEXT 305 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 " at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "
6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is given by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "n
Ck=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF
*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 290 10 "State the " }{TEXT 289 16 "Binomi
al Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 306 31 "and use Maple to demonstrat
e it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "sum(binomial(n,k),k=0..n)" "6#
-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/F*;\"\"!F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "  for n=1 \+
to 10.  Here the symbol " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Sigma;" "6#%&SigmaG" }{TEXT 
-1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma) stands for sum.   (See the worksheet SumS
eq.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 287 
59 "What general formula do the above calculations in  suggest?" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "5.  Pasc
al's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use Mapl
e to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick will
 be to get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Maple \+
command for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(expres
sion(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with index i a
nd m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}
